class Solution {
    public int maxArea(int[] height) {
        int left = 0;             
        int right = height.length - 1;  
        int maxWater = 0;         
        
        while (left < right) {
            int width = right - left;
            
            int h = Math.min(height[left], height[right]);
            
            int water = width * h;
            
            maxWater = Math.max(maxWater, water);
            
            if (height[left] < height[right]) {
                left++;
            } else {
                right--;
            }
        }
        
        return maxWater;
    }
}
APPROACH:Two-Pointer Technique

Instead of checking all pairs (which would take O(n²)), you use a greedy + two-pointer approach to reduce it to O(n).
